    {
      "id": "vscode-node-plugin-root",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "üß© VSCode .node Plugin",
      "position": {
        "x": -420,
        "y": -260
      },
      "width": 520,
      "height": 260,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "# VSCode .node Plugin\n\nGoal: **edit .node files with local filesystem access and instant updates**.\n\nThis plugin is the authoring surface for Twilite node files."
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "vscode-node-plugin-requirements",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "‚úÖ Requirements",
      "position": {
        "x": 160,
        "y": -261
      },
      "width": 420,
      "height": 260,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Requirements\n\n- Open `.node` files with custom editor\n- Local file access (read/write)\n- Instant updates (file watcher + save)\n- JSON validation + errors inline\n- Schema hints (nodes/edges/contracts)\n- Works offline"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "vscode-node-plugin-features",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "‚ú® Core Features",
      "position": {
        "x": -420,
        "y": 40
      },
      "width": 520,
      "height": 280,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Core Features\n\n- Graph preview panel (render nodegraph)\n- Split view: JSON + visual\n- Live sync: edits in either view update the other\n- Quick actions: add node/edge/handle\n- Node type picker from dictionary/manifest\n- Validate before save"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "vscode-node-plugin-architecture",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "üèóÔ∏è Architecture",
      "position": {
        "x": 160,
        "y": 40
      },
      "width": 420,
      "height": 280,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Architectur e\n\n- VSCode extension (webview)\n- Uses file watcher + document provider\n- Parses/serializes `.node` JSON\n- Reuses Twilite renderer where possible\n- Local-only execution (no network required)"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "vscode-node-plugin-security",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "üîí Security + Trust",
      "position": {
        "x": -444.83123268113434,
        "y": 400.6024212217768
      },
      "width": 520,
      "height": 240,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Security\n\n- No remote fetch by default\n- File access limited to workspace\n- Explicit opt-in for external refs\n- Sanitize any embedded HTML/SVG\n\nKeep the editor safe by default."
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "vscode-node-plugin-open-questions",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "‚ùì Answers + Open Items",
      "position": {
        "x": 160,
        "y": 360
      },
      "width": 420,
      "height": 220,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Answers + Open Items\n\n1) **Auto-generate manifests** on new files. Allow easy overwrite. LLMs may author/refresh manifests when appropriate.\n2) **Schema bundling**: unclear (needs clarification).\n3) **Refs resolution**: **local paths resolve locally** (relative to the current .node). **Remote URLs resolve remotely**. No extra fallback needed.\n4) **Multi-graph files**: treat as **one graph** with clusters; **one manifest per graph**. Different manifest ‚áí different graph."
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "vscode-node-plugin-missing-features",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "üß© Missing Features",
      "position": {
        "x": 160,
        "y": 620
      },
      "width": 520,
      "height": 280,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Missing Features\n\n**Now (MVP):**\n- **File association + icon** for `.node` (use `public/logo_light.svg` as default icon)\n\n**Later (post-MVP):**\n- Validation pipeline (contract checks on open/save)\n- Schema/source indicator (local vs remote)\n- External change handling (reload/merge prompt)\n- Clipboard import/export for nodegraph-data\n- Performance safeguards (debounce parsing/rendering)\n- CSP + sanitization for HTML/SVG previews\n- Handle/edge helpers (quick-create, ref validation)"
      }
    }
